@node WhatIsIt "What IS Snapper anyway?"
                                What Is Snapper?

Snapper is a little commodity that lets you snapshot the position of any window
on-screen simply by pressing a hotkey. It's a bit like MUI's snapshot feature,
only it works with all windows, not just MUI ones.

To snapshot a window, it must have a title which is the same every time it
opens. A list of window titles is kept in memory along with the window
dimensions, and this can be edited in the preferences.

I developed Snapper because despite it being an obvious use for a commodity,
there are very few around (I couldn't find any on Aminet). Although it isn't
going to be used all the time, it can be very useful when you do need it.

@endnode

@node Requirements "Requirements..."
                                  @{b}Requirements@{ub}

To use MPackMUI, you will need:

    * OS 3.5

    * MUI V3.8 (probably works with older versions)

@endnode

