@node SecretPage "How did you find this???"
                                @{b}The Secret Page@{ub}

Hi. Either you've just discovered this page or you're a regular here. Today,
I'll tell you about the Psion 5MX.

This cool little computer comes with 16MB of RAM, and a 10MB ROM for storing the
programs. The screen is LCD, fairly wide and has a backlight. You get a "sonic
screwdriver" pen to press the screen with, which is gr8 fun. A mains PSU is also
available.

You get the following programs:

Word     (a word processor, not directly MS Word compatible)
Sheet    (a spreadsheet)
Contacts (an address book)
Agenda   (a personal organiser)
Email    (a built-in, basic email program)
Calc     (a calculator)
Jotter   (a notepad)
Spell    (a fully-fledged dictionary and thesaurus)
Program  (a BASIC-style programming language)
Data     (a database)
Record   (a sound-recording program)
Time     (a world time program)
Bombs    (the all-important Minesweeper game)
Sketch   (a drawing program)
Comms    (a powerful comms program)

On top of this, a Web browser is provided on CD for you to install on the Psion.
All operations are fairly fast, probably equivalent to about a good 68030.

The Psion comes with an Infrared port, which lets you communicate with other
Psions (very easily) and also, wait for it, infrared mobile phones! So if you've
got a mobile with an infrared port and modem (probably cost you about Ł70), you
can surf the net!

All this for the measly price of Ł400. Get one NOW!

Anyway, enough waffle. Enjoy!

ToneMaster, 2000

@endnode
